6:
Later, you covered the earth with a flood, like a blanket;
\q2 and the water covered the mountains.
\q1

10:
You make springs to pour water into ravines;
\q2 their water flows down between the mountains.
\q1

11:
Those streams provide water for all the animals to drink;
\q2 the wild donkeys drink the water and are no longer thirsty.
\q1
